  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Pakistan Monsoon Floods Appeal 2010</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Following heavy monsoonal rain and flash flooding in the north and centre of the country, Red Cross launched the Pakistan Monsoon Floods Appeal 2010 .Funding under this initiative represents the Queensland Government&apos;s donation Australian Red Cross appeal to assist in the relief effort as a results of the 2010 monsson floods in Pakistan. More than 20 million people were affected, many severely, by the floods. Red Cross has assisted millions of people with food, water, shelter and health services. The Red Cross focus supported communities to recover and strengthen their resilience to future disasters through stronger, more flood-resistant housing and psychosocial support.</narrative>
  </description>
